  "text": "AF is frequently associated with LV systolic dysfunction or its exacerbation by worsening haemodynamics, sympathetic activation, [CITATION_1] and by tachycardia-induced cardiomyopathy. [CITATION_2] Tachycardiainduced cardiomyopathy is a condition in which atrial or ventricular tachyarrhythmias or frequent ventricular ectopy result in left ventricular (LV) dysfunction, leading to systolic HF. The hallmark of this condition is partial or complete reversibility once arrhythmia control is achieved. Tachycardia-induced cardiomyopathy can be classified into two categories: one in which arrhythmia is the sole reason for ventricular dysfunction (arrhythmia induced) and another in which the arrhythmia exacerbates ventricular dysfunction and/or worsens HF in a patient with concomitant heart disease (arrhythmia mediated).",
